#sample mean
ipcs_sample_mean <- describe(ipcs_wide_sit %>% select(Sociability:CrtvImagination)) %>%
  select(mean)


profile_plot_fnc <- function(df){
  df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10), legend.position = "none") +
    labs(title = "Aggregated IPCS Facet Means") +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 3.8, xmax = 6.2, ymin = 46, ymax = 93, fill = "green", alpha = .2) +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 0.8, xmax = 3.2, ymin = 25, ymax = 77, fill = "red", alpha = .2) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(3.5, 6.5, 9.5, 12.5), size = 0.25, alpha = 0.8) +
    annotate("text", x = 2, y = 102, size = 2.5,label = "Extraversion") +
    annotate("text", x = 5, y = 102, size = 2.5,label = "Agreeableness") +
    annotate("text", x = 8, y = 102, size=  2.5, label = "Conscientiousness") +
    annotate("text", x = 11, y = 102, size = 2.5, label = "Emotional Stability") +
    annotate("text", x = 14, y = 102, size = 2.5, label = "Openness")
}

ipcs_sample_mean$facet <- rownames(ipcs_sample_mean)
ipcs_sample_mean$facet <- factor(ipcs_sample_mean$facet, levels = c("Sociability", "EnergyLevel", "Assertive", "Trust", "Respect", "Compassion", "Productivity", "Responsibility", "Organization", "Depression_r", "Anxiety_r", "EmotionalVol_r", "IntCuriosity", "AesthSense", "CrtvImagination"))
ipcs_sample_mean <- ipcs_sample_mean %>% rename(value = mean) %>% mutate(Profiles = 1)
profile_plot_fnc(ipcs_sample_mean)

longer version of mc and add traits for plotting

Code
mc_long <- mc %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(-SID, -Profiles, -size, -prop_new, -nrows)
               , names_to = "facet"
               , values_to = "value"
  ) %>%
  mutate(trait = rep(c(rep("Extraversion", 3), 
                       rep("Agreeableness", 3), 
                       rep("Conscientiousness", 3), 
                       rep("Emotional Stability", 3), 
                       rep("Openness",3)), 
                     nrow(mc)))

#make facets ordered factor
mc_long$facet <- factor(mc_long$facet, levels = c("Sociability", "EnergyLevel", "Assertive", "Trust", "Respect", "Compassion", "Productivity", "Responsibility", "Organization", "Depression_r", "Anxiety_r", "EmotionalVol_r", "IntCuriosity", "AesthSense", "CrtvImagination"))

Plot Fnc

Code
profile_plot_fnc <- function(df){
  df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10), legend.position = "top") +
    labs(title = paste0("Participant ", df$SID, "\nn = ", as.character(df$nrows))) +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 3.8, xmax = 6.2, ymin = 46, ymax = 93, fill = "green", alpha = .2) +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 0.8, xmax = 3.2, ymin = 25, ymax = 77, fill = "red", alpha = .2) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(3.5, 6.5, 9.5, 12.5), size = 0.25, alpha = 0.8) +
    annotate("text", x = 2, y = 102, size = 3,label = "Extraversion", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 5, y = 102, size = 3,label = "Agreeableness", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 8, y = 102, size=  3, label = "Conscientiousness", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 11, y = 102, size = 3, label = "Emotional Stability", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 14, y = 102, size = 3, label = "Openness", fontface = "bold")
}

Code
#sample mean
exemplar_sample_mean <- describe(ipcs_wide_sit %>%
                               filter(SID ==214) %>%
                                        select(Sociability:CrtvImagination)) %>%
  select(mean)

#colors
gg_color_hue <- function(n) {
  hues = seq(15, 375, length = n + 1)
  hcl(h = hues, l = 65, c = 100)[1:n]
}

profile_plot_fnc <- function(df){
  df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) + 
    scale_colour_manual(values=c(gg_color_hue(3),"black")) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 8),
          legend.text=element_text(size=10),
          legend.position = "top") +
    #labs(title = "Aggregated IPCS Facet Means") +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 3.8, xmax = 6.2, ymin = 46, ymax = 93, fill = "green", alpha = .2) +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 0.8, xmax = 3.2, ymin = 25, ymax = 77, fill = "red", alpha = .2) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(3.5, 6.5, 9.5, 12.5), size = 0.25, alpha = 0.8) +
    annotate("text", x = 2, y = 102, size = 3,label = "Extraversion", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 5, y = 102, size = 3,label = "Agreeableness", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 8, y = 102, size=  3, label = "Conscientiousness", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 11, y = 102, size = 3, label = "Emotional Stability", fontface = "bold") +
    annotate("text", x = 14, y = 102, size = 3, label = "Openness", fontface = "bold")
}

exemplar_sample_mean$facet <- rownames(exemplar_sample_mean)
exemplar_sample_mean$facet <- factor(exemplar_sample_mean$facet, levels = c("Sociability", "EnergyLevel", "Assertive", "Trust", "Respect", "Compassion", "Productivity", "Responsibility", "Organization", "Depression_r", "Anxiety_r", "EmotionalVol_r", "IntCuriosity", "AesthSense", "CrtvImagination"))
exemplar_sample_mean <- exemplar_sample_mean %>% rename(value = mean) %>% mutate(Profiles = "Person Mean")

#add mean to mc long of 214
mc_214 <- bind_rows(exemplar_sample_mean,
                    mc_long %>% filter(SID == 214))
profile_plot_fnc(mc_214)

Typology plots

Code
# they are in NEOAC order; also, reverse scoring neurocitism
well_adj_vec <- c((6 - 2.38), 3.6, 3.78, 4.19, 3.72)
reserved_vec <- c((6 - 3.21), 2.65, 3.23, 3.6, 3.29)
excitable_vec <- c((6 - 3.69), 3.74, 3.84, 4.10, 3.5)

#EACNO order
index <- c(2,4,5,1,3)
well_adj_vec <- well_adj_vec[index]
reserved_vec <- reserved_vec[index]
excitable_vec <- excitable_vec[index]

#POMP
pomp <- function(x, min, max){
  (x - min)/(max - min)*100
} 

reserved_vec <- pomp(x = reserved_vec, min = 1, max = 5)

well_adj_vec <- pomp(x = well_adj_vec, min = 1, max = 5)

excitable_vec <- pomp(x = excitable_vec, min = 1 , max = 5)

trait_names <- c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Emotional Stability", "Openness")
typ_df <- cbind(c(rep("Reserved", 5), rep("Well-Adjusted", 5), rep("Excitable",5)), c(reserved_vec, well_adj_vec, excitable_vec), rep(trait_names, 3)) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(Profiles = V1,
         value = V2,
         facet = V3) %>%
  mutate(value = as.numeric(value))
typ_df$facet <- factor(typ_df$facet, levels = c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Emotional Stability", "Openness"))


typology_plot <- typ_df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10), legend.position = "top") +
    labs(title = "Trait Typologies from Merz & Roesch")

save(typology_plot, file = "Data/typology_plot.RData")

pdf("z.Plots/Analyses/Merz Roesch Typology Plot.pdf")
print(typology_plot)
dev.off()
quartz_off_screen

Plot classification clusters within individual

Code
#list of participants which have >1 profile
eachLPAindicator <- vector()
eachLPAmulti <- list()
for(i in 1:length(eachLPA)){
  eachLPAindicator[i] <- ( eachLPA[[i]][["G"]] > 1 )
  eachLPAmulti <- eachLPA[eachLPAindicator]
}

#df of participants >1 profile
multiprof <- lpaSummary %>%
  filter(g>1)

clusters.individual.plots <- list()
for(i in 1:length(eachLPAmulti)){
  clusters.individual.plots[[i]] <- fviz_mclust(eachLPAmulti[[i]], what = c("classification", "uncertainty", "BIC"), ellipse.type = "norm", ellipse.level = 0.4, ggtheme = theme_classic(), main = multiprof[i,1])
}

#pdfs of all clusters plots
pdf("z.Plots/Classification Clusters.pdf")
for (i in 1:length(clusters.individual.plots)){
  print(clusters.individual.plots[[i]])
}
dev.off()

plot the BIC of mclust models within individual

bic.individual.plots <- list()
for(i in 1:length(eachLPA)){

                                               what = c("classification", "uncertainty", "BIC"), 
                                               ellipse.type = "norm", ellipse.level = 0.4, 
                                               ggtheme = theme_classic(), 
                                               main = lpaSummary[i,1])
}

```{r}
         facet = V3) %>%
  mutate(value = as.numeric(value))
typ_df$facet <- factor(typ_df$facet, levels = c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Emotional Stability", "Openness"))


typology_plot <- typ_df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10), legend.position = "top") +
    labs(title = "Trait Typologies from Merz & Roesch")

save(typology_plot, file = "Data/typology_plot.RData")

pdf("z.Plots/Analyses/Merz Roesch Typology Plot.pdf")
print(typology_plot)
dev.off()

#all four plot with exemplars trait means; removing merz and roesch from title
typology_plot_four <- typ_df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
```

Plot classification clusters within individual

```{r, eval = FALSE}

#list of participants which have >1 profile
eachLPAindicator <- vector()
eachLPAmulti <- list()
for(i in 1:length(eachLPA)){
  eachLPAindicator[i] <- ( eachLPA[[i]][["G"]] > 1 )
  eachLPAmulti <- eachLPA[eachLPAindicator]
}

#df of participants >1 profile
multiprof <- lpaSummary %>%
  filter(g>1)

clusters.individual.plots <- list()
for(i in 1:length(eachLPAmulti)){
  clusters.individual.plots[[i]] <- fviz_mclust(eachLPAmulti[[i]], what = c("classification", "uncertainty", "BIC"), ellipse.type = "norm", ellipse.level = 0.4, ggtheme = theme_classic(), main = multiprof[i,1])
}

#pdfs of all clusters plots
pdf("z.Plots/Classification Clusters.pdf")
for (i in 1:length(clusters.individual.plots)){
  print(clusters.individual.plots[[i]])
}
dev.off()
```
